  "description": [
    "Jty Tm ANDREW PRICE EDITOR MARLINTON FRIDAY AUG 26 1898 Entered at the postofflce at Marlin ton W Va as second class matter DEMOCRATIC TICKET For Congress Judge DAVID E JOHNSTONE of Mercer Connty For State Senator C W OSENTON of Fayette Connty For House of Delegates I B MOORE of Sunset For Countv Commissioner AMOS BARLOW of Huntersville For Superintendent Free Schools JAMES W WARWICK of Mill Point iFVzy The battle of New Orleans was fought after the signing of the trea ty of peaee because the means of communication were lacking in those days The same thing is true of the late battle of Manila Some of the greatest thinkers say that the United Stutes must keep the Phillipines or cause trou ble in Europe The land grabbers of the Continent will fall out if they are abandoned Should we cast pearls before swine is the question In the Democratic primary of Greenbrier County 1675 votes were cast T H Jarrett and E F Ray mond were nominated for the House of Delegates John H Car away for County Court and L W Burns for Superintendent of Free Schools The Governor of this State has had a prize"
  ],
